<h1>Enterprise Cybersecurity Product Landscape</h1>

<p>
The cybersecurity market is typically organized by security control domains rather than individual vendors.
Below is a structured overview of major cybersecurity product categories deployed in enterprise environments.
</p>

<!-- NETWORK SECURITY -->
<section>
<h2>1. Network Security (Perimeter & Internal Protection)</h2>

<h3>Firewall (NGFW / UTM)</h3>
<p>Controls traffic between networks using policy, application awareness, IPS, and threat intelligence.</p>

<b>Functions:</b>
<ul>
<li>Layer 3–7 traffic filtering</li>
<li>IPS/IDS</li>
<li>Application control</li>
<li>VPN (IPsec / SSL)</li>
<li>Web filtering</li>
</ul>

<b>Examples:</b>
<p>Palo Alto Networks, Fortinet, Check Point Software Technologies, Sophos, Cisco</p>

<b>Related Products:</b>
<ul>
<li>Secure Web Gateway (SWG)</li>
<li>SD-WAN Security</li>
<li>Zero Trust Network Access (ZTNA)</li>
</ul>
</section>

<!-- ENDPOINT SECURITY -->
<section>
<h2>2. Endpoint Security</h2>

<p>Protects laptops, desktops, servers, and mobile endpoints.</p>

<b>Sub-categories:</b>
<ul>
<li>Antivirus / Next-Gen AV</li>
<li>EDR (Endpoint Detection & Response)</li>
<li>XDR (Extended Detection & Response)</li>
</ul>

<b>Capabilities:</b>
<ul>
<li>Malware detection</li>
<li>Behavioral analysis</li>
<li>Ransomware protection</li>
<li>Device isolation</li>
</ul>

<b>Examples:</b>
<p>CrowdStrike, SentinelOne, Microsoft Defender, Trend Micro</p>
</section>

<!-- DLP -->
<section>
<h2>3. Data Loss Prevention (DLP)</h2>

<p>Prevents sensitive data leakage across endpoints, email, cloud, and network channels.</p>

<b>Controls:</b>
<ul>
<li>Data classification</li>
<li>USB/device control</li>
<li>Email inspection</li>
<li>Cloud data monitoring</li>
</ul>

<b>Types:</b>
<ul>
<li>Network DLP</li>
<li>Endpoint DLP</li>
<li>Cloud DLP</li>
</ul>

<b>Examples:</b>
<p>Symantec (Broadcom), Forcepoint, Digital Guardian</p>
</section>

<!-- MDM -->
<section>
<h2>4. Mobile Device Management (MDM) / UEM</h2>

<ul>
<li>Device enrollment</li>
<li>Remote wipe</li>
<li>Policy enforcement</li>
<li>App control</li>
<li>Compliance checks</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Modern Term:</b> Unified Endpoint Management (UEM)</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b> VMware Workspace ONE, Microsoft Intune, Ivanti</p>
</section>

<!-- IAM -->
<section>
<h2>5. Identity and Access Management (IAM)</h2>

<p>Controls who can access what.</p>

<ul>
<li>Authentication</li>
<li>Authorization</li>
<li>SSO (Single Sign-On)</li>
<li>MFA (Multi-Factor Authentication)</li>
<li>Identity governance</li>
</ul>

<b>Extensions:</b>
<ul>
<li>PAM (Privileged Access Management)</li>
<li>CIAM (Customer IAM)</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Examples:</b> Okta, CyberArk, Ping Identity</p>
</section>

<!-- EMAIL SECURITY -->
<section>
<h2>6. Email Security</h2>

<ul>
<li>Anti-phishing</li>
<li>Anti-spam</li>
<li>Attachment sandboxing</li>
<li>URL rewriting</li>
<li>DMARC/DKIM/SPF enforcement</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Examples:</b> Proofpoint, Mimecast, Barracuda Networks</p>
</section>

<!-- VULNERABILITY -->
<section>
<h2>7. Vulnerability & Asset Management</h2>

<ul>
<li>Asset discovery</li>
<li>Vulnerability scanning</li>
<li>Risk scoring</li>
<li>Patch prioritization</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Examples:</b> Tenable, Qualys, Rapid7</p>
</section>

<!-- SOC -->
<section>
<h2>8. Security Operations (SOC Technologies)</h2>

<h3>SIEM</h3>
<p>Centralized log monitoring and correlation.</p>
<p>Examples: Splunk, IBM QRadar, Elastic</p>

<h3>SOAR</h3>
<p>Automated incident response workflows.</p>
</section>

<!-- CLOUD -->
<section>
<h2>9. Cloud Security</h2>

<ul>
<li>CASB</li>
<li>CSPM</li>
<li>CWPP</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Examples:</b> Zscaler, Netskope, Wiz</p>
</section>

<!-- APPSEC -->
<section>
<h2>10. Application Security (AppSec)</h2>

<ul>
<li>Web Application Firewall (WAF)</li>
<li>SAST / DAST</li>
<li>API Security</li>
<li>Runtime protection</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Examples:</b> F5, Akamai Technologies</p>
</section>

<!-- ZERO TRUST -->
<section>
<h2>11. Zero Trust & SASE</h2>

<ul>
<li>SWG</li>
<li>CASB</li>
<li>ZTNA</li>
<li>Firewall-as-a-Service</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Leaders:</b> Palo Alto Networks (Prisma), Fortinet, Zscaler</p>
</section>

<!-- BACKUP -->
<section>
<h2>12. Backup & Ransomware Protection</h2>

<p>Security and recovery combined.</p>
<p><b>Examples:</b> Veeam, Rubrik</p>
</section>

<!-- STACK -->
<section>
<h2>Simplified Enterprise Security Stack</h2>

<ul>
<li>Firewall / SASE</li>
<li>Endpoint EDR/XDR</li>
<li>IAM + MFA</li>
<li>Email Security</li>
<li>DLP</li>
<li>MDM/UEM</li>
<li>Vulnerability Management</li>
<li>SIEM/SOC</li>
<li>Cloud Security</li>
<li>Backup & Recovery</li>
</ul>
</section>

<section class="footer">
Enterprise security protects:
<ul>
<li>Identity → IAM</li>
<li>Device → Endpoint + MDM</li>
<li>Network → Firewall + ZTNA</li>
<li>Data → DLP + Encryption</li>
</ul>
</section>

